<section class="pg-section" data-section="Frequently Asked Questions">
  <h2 class="pg-h">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
  <h2 class="pg-h">What Is PRP Hair Restoration?</h2>
  <h2 class="pg-h">​</h2>
  <p class="pg-text">Platelet-Rich Plasma for Hair (PRP) is an innovative treatment derived from a small sample of your own blood. After collection, your blood is processed in a centrifuge to concentrate the platelets, which contain powerful growth factors essential for tissue regeneration and healing.</p>
  <p class="pg-text">At Menon Medispa, under the direction of regenerative medicine specialist Dr. Aditi Menon, we precisely inject this concentrated PRP solution into targeted areas of your scalp. These growth factors stimulate dormant hair follicles, improve blood circulation, and promote the development of stronger, thicker hair. This natural approach leverages your body's own regenerative capabilities to combat hair thinning and loss.</p>
  <h2 class="pg-h">​​</h2>
  <p class="pg-text">Am I a Good Candidate for PRP Hair Restoration?</p>
  <p class="pg-text">Most people experiencing hair thinning or loss are excellent candidates for PRP treatments. These procedures are particularly effective for:</p>
  <ul class="pg-list">
    <li>Early to moderate stages of pattern baldness (androgenetic alopecia)</li>
    <li>Stress-related hair thinning</li>
    <li>Postpartum hair loss</li>
    <li>Age-related hair thinning</li>
  </ul>
  <p class="pg-text">Ideal candidates are in good overall health without blood clotting disorders or certain autoimmune conditions. Since PRP for hair uses your own blood, the risk of allergic reactions is minimal.</p>
  <p class="pg-text">We recommend scheduling a consultation with Dr. Menon to determine  your specific condition and goals.</p>
  <h2 class="pg-h">What Results Can I Expect?</h2>
  <h2 class="pg-h">​</h2>
  <p class="pg-text">Following PRP hair restoration treatments, you can typically expect:</p>
  <ul class="pg-list">
    <li>Reduced hair shedding within 2-3 weeks</li>
    <li>Increased hair thickness and strength over 2-3 months</li>
    <li>Improved hair growth in previously thinning areas after 4-6 months</li>
    <li>Enhanced overall hair quality and resilience</li>
  </ul>
  <p class="pg-text">For optimal results, we generally recommend a series of 3 treatments spaced 4-6 weeks apart, followed by maintenance sessions every 6-12 months. <br />​​</p>
</section>

